         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">18/9/94 ¶  ¶ This time, noble friend, I approach you only with one question, it is this. ¶  ¶ What is the practical result of the use of  ¶ Rumex hymenosepalus ¶  in the tanneries of California? ¶  ¶ ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">94.09.18a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Eugene Hilgard</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Bancroft Library, University of California, Berkeley, California.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">18/9/94<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Annotated: 'A. Nov. 8'.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Diesmal, edler Freund, nahe ich mich Ihnen nur mit einer Vorfrage, es ist diese.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Was ist das practische Ergebniss der Anwendung von <name key="Rumex%20hymenosepalus">Rumex hymenosepalus</name> in den Gerbereien Californiens?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Schliesst sich das Tannin dieses Rumex am nächsten dem der Eiche, oder der Acacien, oder des Rhus oder einer anderen Tannin Sorte an. Dies zu wissen ist ja von grosser Wichtigkeit, um eine Idee von dem wahre Werth dieser neue Gerbewurzel zu erlangen. Ich habe Samen hier vertheilt, würde aber für etwas mehr frische Samen, die dieser Herbst dort reiften, recht verpflichtet sein.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Sie ehrend, der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">18/9/94</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This time, noble friend, I approach you only with one question, it is this.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>What is the practical result of the use of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Rumex%20hymenosepalus">Rumex hymenosepalus</name>
               </seg> in the tanneries of California?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Is the tannin of this <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Rumex</seg> closest to that of the oak, or the Acaciae or the Rhus or one of the other tannin types. To know this is indeed of great importance to get an idea of the true worth of this new tanning root.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In the next edition of his <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Select plants</seg>, (B95.08.04), p. 479, M added to his note on <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Rumex%20hymenosepalus">Rumex hymenosepalus</name>
                     </seg> information supplied by Hilgard that in tanning, 'the root is best used fresh or converted into an extract, as in drying it deteriorates'.</p>
               </note> I have distributed seeds here but would be very obliged for some more fresh seeds that ripen there this autumn.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Respectfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Rumex%20hymenosepalus">Rumex hymenosepalus</name>
            </p>
         </div>
